race.comment: PERFECT NIGHT (11) finished sixth two runs back then did well last start but found one better over 1547m at Geelong, beaten only a nose. Has the ability to produce another positive result and looks to have been crying out for this trip. JENNI BASSETT (9) knuckled down strongly to get within 1.3 lengths of the winner in second last start over 1440m at Geelong when resuming after a break. Sure to go well again. REGAL GENT (14) finished second last time over 1300m at this track, beaten 3.5 lengths. Beautifully placed and is sure to give this a mighty shake. GRINZINGER TUNDRA (3) was prominent at the turn and finished third last time over 1460m at Kilmore, beaten 2.25 lengths. Placed to advantage so expect a big run.
